The staff at the desk were excellent; they all seem to be willing to answer our questions, help us make dinner reservations, and find our way around.	The staff was very friendly and helpful, getting us tickets to a nearby concert of music by Vivaldi in Chiesa San Vidal and restaurant reservations.	The one point to mention is that the stairs are narrow and not easy to use if you wake up at night, so consider whether you really need a duplex before booking this room.	Note for all that have trouble with stairs that though there are elevators to the rooms/suites ,there were stairs within some units so check before booking!